JOHANNESBURG A taxi overturned on the N2 South-bound highway in Galleria, KwaZulu-Natal on Monday morning leaving 17 passengers injured.ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics found the taxi lying on its roof in the middle of the highway. The occupants had already climbed out of the vehicle.Paramedics found that 17 people had been injured. Their injuries ranged from minor to serious.READ: 17 injured in three-vehicle KZN crashParamedics had to provide a seriously injured patient with advanced life support interventions. Once treated, the patients were transported to various hospitals in the area, said Meiring.The cause of the crash is yet to be established but local authorities were on the scene.African News Agency